text.section:
The services to which this section applies are:
A physical examination to gather information and evidence as to the alleged crime;
Emergency hospital treatment and follow-up medical testing for up to 90 days after the initial physical examination in paragraph (1) of this subsection; and
For up to 5 hours of professional time to gather information and evidence as to the alleged sexual abuse, an initial assessment of a victim of alleged child sexual abuse by:
A physician;
Qualified hospital health care personnel;
A mental health professional; or
An interdisciplinary team expert in the field of child abuse.
